ads from instrumented contexts. I wonder if there’s a way to examine how tests for other classes handled `Class.forName`. It seems like an important aspect to consider, and I'll need to look into it to understand the situation better.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_wAeOGJuYAzjzzmMllRO3fp8x|fc_060d739afd210fe4016a00f146fcac8190bbbcb9979444ed36", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"class\\$|resolveWithCompilerGenerated|Class.forName|forName\" tests/src -g '*Test.java' | head -100"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 808, "output": 1543, "cacheRead": 47104, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 49455, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778446636029, "responseId": "resp_060d739afd210fe4016a00f12d39908190b6c240ef2d8c3cca"}}
