[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing class loading behavior**\n\nI'm exploring how the generated helper might be affected by the absence of a line number and whether tracer filters impact the call stack. I wonder if `Class.forName` only gets intercepted when a class isn't already loaded. Maybe all classes are initially loaded during instrumentation? If they are, does `Class.forName` still get called without a dynamic event? It seems the native agent only logs when a class is missing, so I need to test a target external JDK class to check.\n\n**Exploring class loading methods**\n\nI’m thinking that closure might be loading in a way that isn't instrumented. It could be related to how `MethodHandles.lookup().findClass` functions when it loads from instrumented contexts. I wonder if there’s a way to examine how tests for other classes handled `Class.forName`. It seems like an important aspect to consider, and I'll need to look into it to understand the situation better.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_060d739afd210fe4016a00f12eefb88190bc9ec526ac93c64a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqAPFGwa8ZTfFLSqoAbAUVGdiOsclSwt_WpkzVkHVwqLA_O9FkjItd6FwucD_keoGAqAibFDdvcwnnGFvY9G4-epeUZd788Lvj5T-PsHAcPbgRqiHkZQXWgr_kOuiJa3UrpJ0p0ZkR168EXy-tfgkUuQgfxfZOcdxM-GPZcK4_MWbJoUJpF5HfVccxP6sO8rHZHVGUB4aq7BMBU92ikTyGP6quv36RA-vTTTjRFFdtJaCnJ76B7bNh2kU-1rl-iXRMYHWnN5H2L3fBUUJN0B8ExvOl7-bGWtGiqXPHYGEiy1tvS9LXNP_haOYiVN8GXk-o7WxGcpuUcOHLun4j1B5PvhHmx76XZCehh5hM0lPYERopdkFqdDvl6M9cWR93S8RJRThNynTDh9V3Etw0t1509vELrIelo6J-uvUqC1h9pJHcvlWaVnoYxW0vVEI085gGp6XdIgfD7DQ3ob8fCxN_AYKf-ts5RKyt12nwDlQxPqzaS5b4a9YnFdfqH85v2PjwyG5kH2ybEPcTU8k05CtrApEcpWRWm1iWUzvtKlHZtlFNVvKFlMk4-t2MoUowtLu8Keyn7_QhGMuUgd1UV1Zh-0Cq1ZWuKBScPthBQajlYzTmbUudjsWcU9Ap8LZ4AovkKesVWMBu9JKPxFOU_8EUXf0bC_sAmxmpNTS_xXOYGwPsVFvkMp8_S8yBq-G4Bq4pRZf03O0264GKO-MQHlTDnLWpH4HbTs5IdPnfhX3Ie-Hbn89v9AsjfkYDBiCj54Yn9HMDu1YISH1Awe8-CcpojiLe