 from instrumented contexts. I wonder if there’s a way to examine how tests for other classes handled `Class.forName`. It seems like an important aspect to consider, and I'll need to look into it to understand the situation better.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_wAeOGJuYAzjzzmMllRO3fp8x|fc_060d739afd210fe4016a00f146fcac8190bbbcb9979444ed36", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"class\\$|resolveWithCompilerGenerated|Class.forName|forName\" tests/src -g '*Test.java' | head -100"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 808, "output": 1543, "cacheRead": 47104, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 49455, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778446636029, "responseId": "resp_060d739afd210fe4016a00f12d39908190b6c240ef2d8c3cca"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_wAeOGJuYAzjzzmMllRO3fp8x|fc_060d739afd210fe4016a00f146fcac8190bbbcb9979444ed36", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/org.eclipse.jdt.core.compiler/ecj/4.4.2/src/test/java/org_eclipse_jdt_core_compiler/ecj/ErrorTypeElementTest.java:158:                    final MissingTypeMarker[] annotationsByType = missingSuperclass\ntests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-script-runtime/2.3.20/src/test/java/org_jetbrains_kotlin/kotlin_script_runtime/Kotlin_script_runtimeTest.java:186:        AcceptedAnnotations methodAcceptedAnnotations = CustomAnnotatedTemplate.class\ntests/src/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty/hadoop-shaded-protobuf_3_7/1.1.1/src/test/java/org_apache_hadoop_thirdparty/hadoop_shaded_protobuf_3_7/GeneratedMessageTest.java:65:                TrackedMessageBuilder.class\ntests/src/org.apache.hadoop.thirdparty/hadoop-shaded-protobuf_3_7/1.1.1/src/test/java/org_apache_hadoop_thirdparty/hadoop_shaded_protobuf_3_7/ByteBufferWriterTest.java:20:        Class<?> writerClass = Class.forName(\ntests/src/org.apache.hadoop.thirdp